In src/eval/memory/heap.rs:519-531, the sweep phase pops all blocks from rest, checks recyclability, and pushes to either recycled or unusable. This is O(blocks) with poor cache locality due to LinkedList traversal.

```rust
pub fn sweep(&mut self) {
    let mut unusable: LinkedList<BumpBlock> = LinkedList::default();
    while let Some(mut block) = self.rest.pop_front() {
        if block.recycle() {
            self.recycled.push_back(block);
        } else {
            unusable.push_back(block);
        }
    }
    self.rest.append(&mut unusable);
}
```

**Fix:** Use Vec instead of LinkedList for better cache locality.

**Source:** Performance Review hq-leg-om5os

In src/eval/stg/string.rs:45-58, the regex caching function clones the key string twice when inserting:
```rust
let key = text.as_ref().to_string();  // First allocation
if !rcache.contains(&key) {
    let re = Regex::new(text.as_ref()).map_err(|_| ExecutionError::BadRegex(key.clone()))?;
    rcache.put(key.clone(), re);  // Second clone
}
```

**Fix:** Use entry API or restructure to avoid double cloning.

**Source:** Performance Review hq-leg-om5os

Metadata-driven argument parsing built on top of __ARGS. Supports type validation, help generation, short/long options. Example:

```eu
{
  args: {
    input: { type: "string", help: "Input file path" }
    verbose: { type: "bool", short: "v", help: "Enable verbose output" }
    count: { type: "int", default: 1 }
  }
}
```

